#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn56.38"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn56.38:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 56 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 56 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn56.38:0.2"
msgid "4. Sīsapāvanavagga "
msgstr "4. In a Rosewood Forest "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
#. VAR: 38. Dutiyasūriyasutta → dutiyasuriyūpamasuttaṃ (bj) | suriyupamā 2 (pts1)
msgctxt "sn56.38:0.3"
msgid "38. Dutiyasūriyasutta "
msgstr "38. The Simile of the Sun (2nd) "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1
msgctxt "sn56.38:1.1"
msgid "“Yāvakīvañca, bhikkhave, candimasūriyā loke nuppajjanti, neva tāva mahato ālokassa pātubhāvo hoti mahato obhāsassa. "
msgstr "“Mendicants, as long as the moon and the sun don’t arise in the world, no great light or great radiance appears. "

#. VAR: Andhatamaṃ → andhantamaṃ (bj, pts1)
msgctxt "sn56.38:1.2"
msgid "Andhatamaṃ tadā hoti andhakāratimisā. "
msgstr "Darkness prevails then, utter darkness. "

#. VAR: rattindivā → rattidivā (pts1, mr)
msgctxt "sn56.38:1.3"
msgid "Neva tāva rattindivā paññāyanti, na māsaddhamāsā paññāyanti, na utusaṃvaccharā paññāyanti. "
msgstr "Day and night aren’t found, nor months and fortnights, nor seasons and years. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli5.443, sc2
msgctxt "sn56.38:2.1"
msgid "Yato ca kho, bhikkhave, candimasūriyā loke uppajjanti, atha mahato ālokassa pātubhāvo hoti mahato obhāsassa. "
msgstr "But when the moon and the sun arise in the world, a great light, a great radiance appears. "

msgctxt "sn56.38:2.2"
msgid "Neva andhakāratamaṃ tadā hoti na andhakāratimisā. "
msgstr "Darkness no longer prevails. "

msgctxt "sn56.38:2.3"
msgid "Atha rattindivā paññāyanti, māsaddhamāsā paññāyanti, utusaṃvaccharā paññāyanti. "
msgstr "Day and night are found, and months and fortnights, and seasons and years. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn56.38:2.4"
msgid "Evameva kho, bhikkhave, yāvakīvañca tathāgato loke nuppajjati arahaṃ sammāsambuddho, neva tāva mahato ālokassa pātubhāvo hoti mahato obhāsassa. "
msgstr "In the same way, as long as the Realized One doesn’t arise in the world, no great light or great radiance appears. "

msgctxt "sn56.38:2.5"
msgid "Andhatamaṃ tadā hoti andhakāratimisā. "
msgstr "Darkness prevails then, utter darkness. "

msgctxt "sn56.38:2.6"
msgid "Neva tāva catunnaṃ ariyasaccānaṃ ācikkhaṇā hoti desanā paññāpanā paṭṭhapanā vivaraṇā vibhajanā uttānīkammaṃ. "
msgstr "There’s no explanation of the four noble truths, no teaching, advocating, establishing, clarifying, analyzing, and revealing of them. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "sn56.38:3.1"
msgid "Yato ca kho, bhikkhave, tathāgato loke uppajjati arahaṃ sammāsambuddho, atha mahato ālokassa pātubhāvo hoti mahato obhāsassa. "
msgstr "But when the Realized One arises in the world, a great light, a great radiance appears. "

msgctxt "sn56.38:3.2"
msgid "Neva andhatamaṃ tadā hoti na andhakāratimisā. "
msgstr "Darkness no longer prevails. "

msgctxt "sn56.38:3.3"
msgid "Atha kho catunnaṃ ariyasaccānaṃ ācikkhaṇā hoti desanā paññāpanā paṭṭhapanā vivaraṇā vibhajanā uttānīkammaṃ. "
msgstr "Then there’s the explanation of the four noble truths, the teaching, advocating, establishing, clarifying, analyzing, and revealing of them. "

msgctxt "sn56.38:3.4"
msgid "Katamesaṃ catunnaṃ? "
msgstr "What four? "

msgctxt "sn56.38:3.5"
msgid "Dukkhassa ariyasaccassa … pe … dukkhanirodhagāminiyā paṭipadāya ariyasaccassa. "
msgstr "The noble truths of suffering, its origin, its cessation, and the path. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "sn56.38:4.1"
msgid "Tasmātiha, bhikkhave, ‘idaṃ dukkhan’ti yogo karaṇīyo … pe … ‘ayaṃ dukkhanirodhagāminī paṭipadā’ti yogo karaṇīyo”ti. "
msgstr "That’s why you should practice meditation …” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn56.38:4.2"
msgid "Aṭṭhamaṃ. "
msgstr ""

